3D Fruit Tetris by Song Tung Nguyen (301354423)
*Instructions:
- The program runs on Linux OS and requires GLEW and freeglut installed.
- freeglut: Type "sudo apt-get install freeglut3-dev" on terminal.
- GLEW: Type "sudo apt-get install libglew-dev" on terminal or follow the instructions on "http://glew.sourceforge.net/index.html"
- To run the program, please head into the folder "Assignment 2/Part 1" and type "make" (ignores all the warnings) anf type "./FruitTetris3D" to run the program.

*Controls:
- Up arrow to rotate the tile.
- Down arrow to move the tile down faster.
- 'w' to move the arm upwards.
- 's' to move the arm downwards.
- 'a' to move the arm leftwards.
- 'd' to move the arm 'rightwards'.
- ctrl + left arrow would rotate the viewing angle to the left.
- ctrl + right arrow would rotate the viewing angle to the right.
- Press the space bar to drop the tile (after 10 seconds the tile would be dropped automatically).
- 'Q' to quit.
- 'R' to restart.
- Left arrow + Right arrow (movement of the tile to the left and right) is disabled just as the requirements specified.

*Additional Features:
- Fullfiled all the additional features outlied in the assignment.

*Known bugs:
- There are no bugs detected at the moment.

